## Ingredients

Makes enough for ~5-6 pizzas

630 grams strong flour
15 grams sugar (1.5 tablespoons)
10 grams salt
10 grams active dry yeast (2 teaspoons)
32 grams extra virgin olive oil
420 grams lukewarm water

## Recipe

Combine flour, sugar, salt and yeast in bowl and mix

Add olive oil and water. Mix until well combined, leave for 10 minutes

Turn onto surface and knead for 10-15 minutes, until it passes the windowpane test

Divide if necessary, leave to rise in fridge at least 1 day

Remove from fridge, shape into individual balls and leave to rest at room temperature at least two hours before baking






